Armeniis in oris. “ On the borders of Armenia.’' The allusion is to the northern confines. Armenia forms a very elevated plain, surrounded on all sides by lofty mountains, of which Ararat and Kohi- selban are crowned with perpetual snow, The cold in the high districts of the country ie so very intense as to leave only three months sor the season of vegetation, including seed-time and harvest.
